 The petitioner challenged the order of detention on the ground that the autho. rities fixed the maximum period of detention without applying their mind as to, the period of detention.
 
HELD : (i) The order of detention does not suffer from any constitutional infirmity. The authorities have applied their mind while detaining for the maximum period mentioned in the statute. This Court has held in ragu Shaw v. State of West Bengal that the maximum period mentioned in section 13 of the Act as amended by section 6(d) of the Defence of India Act, 1971, is a. constitutionally valid provision.
 [484B; 483G] Fagu Shaw v. The State of West Bengal, [1973] INSC 251; A.I.R. 1974 S.C. 613 followed..
 
